# Maintain FEATURES.md

Before completing any task that changes product behavior, read `docs/FEATURES.md` for context.

**Update `docs/FEATURES.md` in the same change** when you:

- Add, remove, or rename a user-facing feature or flow
- Add or change an API route under `app/api/`
- Add a Supabase migration (append to the migration index)
- Add a response type, delivery mode, or offline/sync behavior
- Add or change environment variables
- Add E2E specs or materially change test coverage scope

Use the checklist at the bottom of `docs/FEATURES.md`. Keep entries concise and path-oriented so future agents can navigate quickly.

Do not skip this because the user did not mention the doc — it is part of the definition of done for feature work.
